HEADWORD: Esparto
<hw>Es*par"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.; cf. L.
<ets>spartum</ets> Spanish broom, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A species of Spanish grass (<spn>Macrochloa tenacissima</spn>), of
which cordage, shoes, baskets, etc., are made. It is also used for
making paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

